kfactory subprocess-delegated token refresh (deployment glue).

Layered on top of the static Bearer and workspace-routing patches.
NOT upstreamable: kfactory-specific paths, exit codes, and a shared
file-cache schema between Go (kfactory) and TS (opencode TUI). Design
rationale + the auth.json schema contract: docs/spec.md §4 in the
kfactory repo; exit codes: cmd/kfactory/exit.go.

What this adds:
  - NEW module packages/core/src/kfactory-bearer-refresh.ts: the shared
    auth.json reader, createBearerRefreshFetch (refresh-aware fetch that
    spawns `kfactory auth refresh` near expiry), and the
    onBearerRefreshHint pub/sub (placement rationale in the module
    header).
  - A toast subscription in packages/tui/src/app.tsx consuming the
    refresh-hint pub/sub (one error toast per failure mode per TUI
    session).
  - OPENCODE_SERVER_BEARER_CACHE_PATH env (core/flag/flag.ts) +
    bearerFromCache() in packages/opencode/src/server/auth.ts so
    ServerAuth.header() picks up a token rotated between the launcher
    exec and the SDK's first request. Fails closed on a broken cache.
    @WARNING: ServerAuth.header() callers at v1.17.4 (re-enumerate on
    every bump; a broken cache makes bearerFromCache throw at all of
    them if the env is set): cli/cmd/attach.ts (the intended one),
    plugin/index.ts inside `opencode serve` (the dangerous one -- a
    globally exported env + broken cache file would fail plugin boot),
    cli/cmd/acp.ts, cli/cmd/run.ts, cli/tui/worker.ts (per RPC fetch).
    The env must only be set by `kfactory attach`, never exported
    globally. NOTE the SEPARATE unpatched ServerAuth fork at
    packages/server/src/auth.ts (consumed by packages/cli's daemon.ts
    + server middleware) -- re-check whether upstream migrates the
    opencode binary's paths onto it on every bump.

kfactory must be on the operator PATH for the subprocess refresh.
Same-machine, same-UID, same-auth.json.

